verbs.description: objectize (third-person singular simple present objectizes, present participle objectizing, simple past and past participle objectized)

entries.meaning: To turn into, or treat as, an object; to objectify.
examples: […]  an indestructible power with two opposite and counteracting forces, which  […]  we may call the centrifugal and centripetal forces. The intelligence in the one tends to objectize itself, and in the other to know itself in the object.
